C-Suite Dashboard for Synvara: Build Plan
This document outlines a comprehensive build plan for creating a daily, weekly, and monthly dashboard user interface for Synvara, based on the provided repository information (daytrader1981/C-Suite-Dashboard). Given the limited information and absence of a specified primary language in the repository, we will assume a modern web stack comprising React for the frontend and Node.js with Express for the backend API. We will also assume that data will be fetched from an external source or database.

1. Architecture Overview
The dashboard will follow a three-tier architecture:

Frontend (React): Responsible for rendering the user interface, handling user interactions, and communicating with the backend API.
Backend (Node.js/Express): Provides API endpoints to serve data to the frontend. It will fetch and process data from the data source.
Data Source: Represents the external database or API providing the necessary data.
The dashboard will consist of three main views: Daily, Weekly, and Monthly. Each view will display key performance indicators (KPIs) relevant to the selected time period.

2. Step-by-Step Implementation Guide
#### 2.1. Backend (Node.js/Express)

##### 2.1.1. Project Setup

mkdir synvara-dashboard-backend
cd synvara-dashboard-backend
npm init -y
npm install express cors dotenv
npm install --save-dev nodemon
##### 2.1.2. Create index.js

// index.js
const express = require('express');
const cors = require('cors');
const dotenv = require('dotenv');
dotenv.config();

const app = express();
const port = process.env.PORT || 3001;

app.use(cors());
app.use(express.json());

// Mock data (replace with actual database/API calls)
const dailyData = {
  date: '2024-10-27',
  revenue: 10000,
  orders: 50,
  customerAcquisitionCost: 200
};

const weeklyData = {
  startDate: '2024-10-21',
  endDate: '2024-10-27',
  revenue: 70000,
  orders: 350,
  customerAcquisitionCost: 1400
};

const monthlyData = {
  month: 'October',
  year: 2024,
  revenue: 300000,
  orders: 1500,
  customerAcquisitionCost: 6000
};

app.get('/api/daily', (req, res) => {
  res.json(dailyData);
});

app.get('/api/weekly', (req, res) => {
  res.json(weeklyData);
});

app.get('/api/monthly', (req, res) => {
  res.json(monthlyData);
});

app.listen(port, () => {
  console.log(Server is running on port ${port});
});

##### 2.1.3. Create .env

PORT=3001
